/SCC/XXOMMENTARY/XX. The traditional wording of Biblical Selection II presents
detailed bountiful or devastating consequences of IsraelÚs collective rela-
tionship to the mitzvot. This biblical section (Deuteronomy 11:13-21)
offers a supernatural theology that many contemporary Jews find difficult.
The biblical section on this page (Deuteronomy 28:1-6, 30:15-19) was
included in the 1945 Reconstructionist Siddur. It begins by encouraging
observance in the same language, but concentrates on the positive ways in
which observance of mitzvot focuses our attention on GodÚs presence as
perceived through productivity and the pursuit of abundant life.    /SC/XXS.S./XX/PR
/PR
/SCK/XXAVANAH/XX. The doctrine of the unity of God calls for the integration of all
lifeÚs purposes into a consistent pattern of thought and conduct.    /SC/XXM.M.K./XX/PR
