/SCC/XXOMMENTARY/XX. The statement of GodÚs oneness unifies not only the con-
text of Shema but the text as well--three scriptural paragraphs specified
in the Mishnah (a second century codification of Jewish law). The power-
ful declaration of GodÚs unity fuses the responsibility to love God and to
study GodÚs teachings (first paragraph) with the lesson that their fulfill-
ment confirms GodÚs presence (second and third paragraphs). Hence, the
unity of God as idea and presence.    /SC/XXS.S./XX/PR
