ÑÖÑâ öÖñé åã / all the mitzvot of /SCT/XXHE /XXE/XXTERNAL /XXO/XXNE/XX. åã, all, as many as
possible. According to rabbinic tradition, there are 613 mitzvot in the
Torah. A combination of gematria (Jewish numerology) and ritual mac-
rame "proves" that öâñâñ / /ITtzitzit/XX equals all 613 mitzvot combined: ñ = 90,
â = 10, ñ = 90, â = 10, ö = 400; all together = 600. Each /ITtzitzit/XX has 8
strands (per corner) and 5 knots; 8 + 5 = 13; 13 + 600 = 613.    /SC/XXL.W.K./XX/PR
